Latest confirmed cases of Covid in SA 8 May 2022 The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD), a division of the National Health Laboratory Service, continues to provide laboratory-based surveillance to inform the public health response towards COVID-19 in South Africa. Today the institute reports 5,486 new COVID-19 cases that have been identified in South Africa, which brings the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases to 3 841 388. This increase represents a 25.3% positivity rate. Today, the National Department of Health (NDoH) reports 7 deaths and of these, 5 occurred in the past 24 – 48 hours. This brings the total fatalities to 100,523 to date. 24 675 963 tests have been conducted in both public and private sectors as per the table below. Sector Total tested New tested Private 13,453,057 54.5% 14,316 66.0% Public 11,222,906 45.5% 7,376 34.0% Total 24,675,963 100.0% 21,692 100.0% PROVINCIAL BREAKDOWN The majority of new cases today are from Gauteng Province (40%) followed by KwaZulu-Natal (26%). Western Cape accounted for 17%; Free State accounted for 5%; Eastern Cape and North West each accounted for 3% respectively; Mpumalanga and Northern Cape each accounted for 2% respectively; and Limpopo accounted for <1% of today’s new cases. The cumulative number of cases by province are shown in the table below: Province Total cases for 07 May 2022 Adjusted numbers after harmonisation Updated total cases on 07 May 2022 Incident infections for 08 May 2022 Possible reinfections for 08 May 2022 New cases on 08 May 2022 Total cases for 08 May 2022 Percentage total Eastern Cape 350953 0 350953 151 24 175 351128 9.1 Free State 206708 0 206708 226 54 280 206988 5.4 Gauteng 1262405 0 1262405 1878 335 2213 1264618 32.9 KwaZulu-Natal 688750 0 688750 1246 206 1452 690202 18.0 Limpopo 157043 0 157043 22 2 24 157067 4.1 Mpumalanga 196054 0 196054 88 24 112 196166 5.1 North West 195523 0 195523 167 23 190 195713 5.1 Northern Cape 110281 0 110281 112 19 131 110412 2.9 We